File: Rand Water is embarking on a 54-hour planned water shutdown which is expected to affect numerous areas’ reservoirs and water supply. JOHANNESBURG - Rand Water is embarking on a 54-hour planned water shutdown which is expected to affect numerous areas’ reservoirs and water supply. In a statement released on Monday Johannesburg Water explained that a valve needs to be replaced on the B11 pipeline, which will result in limited water supply. LIVEBLOG: Residents gear up for #TshwaneShutdown "Rand Water is planning a shutdown on the B11 pipeline to install a 2000mm valve and this will result in limited water supply from Rand Water", read the statement. Residents are urged to use water sparingly. The following municipalities are expected to be affected: